to the editor re cancer painkillers pose new abuse threat front page feb 9 illegal sales and abuse of cancer painkillers represent a serious health threat and a challenge to both doctors and law enforcement pain is a common side effect in cancer treatment in fact cancer patients often fear pain more than the disease itself while fear of addiction has long been a barrier to effective pain treatment it should not continue to compromise the care of millions of americans who have a right to pain relief as medical professionals and health advocates we have a duty to protect that right paul hyman md bay shore ny feb 10 2001 the writer is chief medical spokesman american cancer society of new york and new jersey

